EQUINE HERPESVIRUS, EQUINE - NORTH AMERICA (05): USA (ARIZONA)
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 28 Jan 2016
Source: AZ Central, Associated Press report [edited]
http://www.azcentral.com/story/news/local/phoenix/2016/01/28/all-horses-at-phoenix-racetrack-placed-on-21-day-quarantine/79490620/


All horses at a Phoenix [Arizona] racetrack [Turf Paradise] have been placed on a 21-day quarantine effective immediately.

Arizona Department of Agriculture officials said Thursday [28 Jan 2016] that one horse at Turf Paradise showed signs of a highly contagious equine virus.

During the quarantine, racing will continue as scheduled but no horses will be allowed in or out of the facility.

Turf Paradise General Manager Vince Francia says the suspected case of equine herpesvirus is linked to an outbreak in New Mexico.

The EHV-1 virus can cause severe neurological problems in horses, but doesn't affect humans.

Turf Paradise recently received 3 horses from New Mexico's Sunland Park Racetrack.

Last Friday [22 Jan 2016], track officials at Sunland Park suspended all racing for at least 2 weeks after 5 horses were found to have the virus.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[For information on this disease, readers are encouraged to read my moderator comment in ProMED-mail post 20160124.3960827.

This is a very serious disease. It should not be taken lightly that this area is under quarantine.

Hopefully, someone is taking the temperature of these horses at least twice a day and recording it to determine whether it changes from one day to the next -- without depending on their memory. A slight rise in body temperature may be the earliest indication of this disease. - Mod.TG

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3976987,207.]
